dcterms:description: MultiWOZ 2.2 is a human-to-human, multi-domain, task-oriented dialogue dataset featuring over 10,000 dialogues spanning 8 domains. It provides a well-formatted schema for the dialogue state tracking (DST) task, including domain and slot descriptions and possible values for categorical slots.
dcterms:title: MultiWOZ 2.2

dcterms:description: M2M contains 3000 simulated dialogues from 2 domains, which are later refined by humans. It is used to evaluate the ability to track dialogue states across various dialogue domains.
dcterms:title: M2M

dcterms:description: WOZ 2.0 is built from a Wizard-Of-Oz (WOZ) experiment where users type text in their queries instead of relying on speech inputs, thus having more complex dialogue contexts.
dcterms:title: WOZ 2.0
